Subject: SLIP problem
Date: 24 Nov 93 16:15:11 GMT

Hi folks,

I'm a new Linux user (just got it from Linux Systems) and one of the
first things I'm trying to get working is telnet over SLIP.  Last night
was the first time I got far enough to get a telnet session thru the SLIP
server started, but as soon as the session started I kept getting errors
about data fragmentation which eventually led my telnet session to end.. 
I looked in the Net-2 HOWTO and found a bug description that said that IP
fragmentation is not supported in Net-2d but that it should be supported
in Net-2e.  Can anyone tell me: 1) how I can verify that I have net-2d,  
2) if there's any way around this problem in net-2d by setting
appropriate configuration options, or 3) is Net-2e available yet, if so
where can I get it...

thnx

